The latest Africa Wealth Report for 2022 published by New World Wealth shows that much wealth still resides in South African cities notably Johannesburg and surrounds, and Cape Town. The report revealed that five of South Africa’s cities place within the top 10 of Africa’s most wealthy. The coastal cities of Durban and Umhlanga were in fifth place followed by the capital city, Pretoria in seventh. “Despite a tough decade to date, South Africa is still home to more than twice as many millionaires as any other African country,” said New World Wealth in partnership with Henley & Partners. It said that South Africa continues to attract high net worth individuals (HNWIS) due to its weather and environment, well-established top-end residential areas such as Camps Bay, a large stock exchange, free media and a well-developed banking system and wealth management sector.
